post_text:
Greetings to all Voyageurs Families/Students,

I just wanted to provide you with an update as to how things are going in the preparation of what ways we might be having school this fall. Our deepest hope is that we all can be back together again at one time but we also need to prepare for combinations of that as well as distance learning.
As far we know there will be an announcement next week that will identify how the school year will start this fall. We’ve had many meetings this summer as we make plans for ways to deliver education and keep all as safe as possible.
We will also be reaching out to each family in the next few weeks to check on your status this fall and answer any questions that you might have. The office is staffed Mon-Thurs from 9am-3pm and we’ll be back to a regular schedule starting August 3rd.
We have added to our website some guidelines from the Minnesota Department of Health that asks all families to prepare for different scenarios should the COVID-19 issue affect you.

Stay safe!
Scott

post_text:
Dear Voyageurs Families/Students:

Yesterday the Governor extended the current Distance Learning Program through the end of the school year. Experts in the Health field have determined that this is the best way to help fight the COVID-19 pandemic.
I recognize that this news might be difficult to hear for our school community and many of us were still hoping to return to our typical Spring time activities.
We will use both May 1 and May 4 as staff training days to fine tune our current Distance Learning Plan. Those days will be non-instructional days for students. Classes will resume on May 5th. We will also keep you updated on any new changes that take place with our plan.
We know that school closures put burdens on children and families. We appreciate your efforts at home to help make this time as successful as possible. We continue to offer resources for both students and parents via our website and “Kelly’s Corner” link as well. We are all here to help. Let us know your thoughts at any time.

Scott

post_text:
Distance learning-Middle School Science with Alison Glade

During our weekly zoom calls I have been finding different ways to engage my students virtually. Past weeks I have done scavenger hunts. This week we are learning about Earth Day in science, so I thought how could I incorporate this into my virtual meeting? Virtual baking was the answer! My students and I talked about different grocery packaging that is reusable or recyclable as we baked sugar cookies that looked like the Earth! The students that participated really enjoyed the break from the regular distance learning too!

Finished product from one of my 7th graders. Yummy

March 15, 2020

Dear Voyageurs Expeditionary School Families,

Governor Walz has announced the closure of all schools to students in Minnesota beginning Wednesday, March 18 through Friday, March 27. Voyageurs Expeditionary School WILL BE in session Monday, March 16 and Tuesday, March 17.

This time will be used by our staff to plan educational services in the event of a longer school closure. We will also be deep cleaning the school.

Bag lunches will be provided for students on a “grab and go” basis.

A parent survey has been posted on the Voyageurs Expeditionary School website to help us prepare for distance learning and know how many daily lunches to prepare. Your participation in the survey is CRITICAL in helping us formulate our plan of action.

As always, our first priority is the safety and well-being of our students. We also want to ensure every child has access to the education they need and deserve.

As more information is made available, we will post on our website, our Facebook page and utilize JMC for messages.

Sincerely,

Scott Anderson, Director

Good Afternoon,

As a requirement for the senior project, each student will present an applied piece that demonstrates their learning and being able to apply their learning to a new situation.

On Tuesday April 23 four of the seniors will be presenting their applied pieces at school. This is your invitation to come and see what they are doing and participate in their applied pieces.

5pm- 7pm Lindsey will have an open art gallery in the HS SS room

5-5:45 Val will present information about missing and murdered indigenous women in the cafeteria

5:45-6:15 Angel will be presenting about the foster care system in the HS resource room

6:15-7:00 Shyanne will be presenting about the environmental effects of tectonic plates in the HS Science room.

Please join us for one or all the presentations! No RSVP needed , just come and support our students as your are able.

post_text: On Aug 1st, one of our students lost his life in an automobile accident. River Ryan joined us this past school year. He had a quiet way about him and was very passionate about anything with wheels. The thoughts and good wishes of the entire Voyageurs family are with him. Condolences can be left on the Holmes Funeral home website.

River Patrick Ryan Obituary - Valentine, NE | ObitTree™
text:
On Aug 1st, one of our students lost his life in an automobile accident. River Ryan joined us this past school year. He had a quiet way about him and was very passionate about anything with wheels. The thoughts and good wishes of the entire Voyageurs family are with him. Condolences can be left on the Holmes Funeral home website.

School bus transportation provided.

We are a FREE, public school serving students in grades 6-12

PLEASE HELP OUT VOYAGEURS!!

Voyageurs Expeditionary School has received $2,500 and are competing for the chance to win an additional $7,500 in the Toyota Drive for Education program.

Voting is now open and runs through March 5.

To vote:

• Log in to Facebook.

• Go to PREP45 and “like” their page.

•Click on the “Minnesota Toyota Drive for Education” Contest button. Here, you may read the nominating essays for each school.

• Then, click on “Vote” on the banner at the top of the page.

The site states only one vote is allowed per entry.

Local nominated projects include a greenhouse for the lunch program at Voyageurs Expeditionary School.

Winners will be announced during the Minnesota State High School Hockey Tournament.
